Certainly! Below is a JavaScript function that retrieves the name of a famous sportsperson who is a role model for children and has won an international championship within the last five years. For this example, let's choose Naomi Osaka, a renowned tennis player who won the US Open in 2018 and 2020, and is admired for her sportsmanship and advocacy.

```javascript
function getRoleModelSportsperson() {
    const sportsperson = {
        name: "Naomi Osaka",
        sport: "Tennis",
        achievements: [
            { title: "US Open", year: 2018 },
            { title: "Australian Open", year: 2019 },
            { title: "US Open", year: 2020 },
            { title: "Australian Open", year: 2021 }
        ],
        roleModel: true
    };

    return sportsperson.name;
}

console.log(getRoleModelSportsperson());
```

This function defines an object representing Naomi Osaka and returns her name. You can modify the function to include other sportspersons by updating the object properties as needed.
